<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the first bytes in a section when GSYM is contained in a section of an</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">/// system as the members were laid out so that they shouldn&#39;t align</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// differently on different architectures.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// When endianness of the system loading a GSYM file matches, the file can</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// be mmap&#39;ed in and a pointer to the header can be cast to the first bytes</Highlight></CodeLine>
